Comment: "Guardians of the Galaxy" is one of the greatest movies of all time. When I first heard of it, and saw the teaser, before it came out, I was very skeptical of it. I wasn't sure if it looked that good, and I thought it looked corny. Then I finally watched the movie, and I had an absolute blast!! This movie was not corny. It was amazing, and had awesome weirdness to it, with a loveliness to it that made me appreciate this movie. It is a fun, hilarious, sci-fi saturated, and action-packed extravaganza!! It was surprisingly touching at times, the sound effects, production design and cinematography were so excellent for this space universe that the creators of this movie created, it was visually amazing, and vibrant. And the music was just so great for this move. The music was perfect for this movie, especially when you find out how the music is involved in the story, I mean the music is already awesome, and the fact that the music itself even incorporates itself into the story is even more awesome!! The characters are so much fun in this movie, and all of the actors play their characters so perfectly. I love this movie so much. Comment: I completely understand that Guardians of the Galaxy was just a movie. And I fully enjoyed it. It was much better than I or most sci-fi fans most likely anticipated. However, despite this movie¬†technically¬†being an action adventure comedy blockbuster, my heart was nearly ripped out in the beginning of the movie¬†from watching the young Peter Quill witnessing his mother's final moments alive. That scene almost caught me off guard and was extremely a bit more emotional than anticipated. I don't think I have had a sci-fi movie hit me emotionally that hard since watching Luke Skywalker's last moments with his father Darth Vader when he lay dying in his son's arms. At the end of the movie, I enjoyed the solid friendship the team finally established with each other. That scene reminds me of some of my closest¬†buddies I grew up with during my teen years. I thank Marvel Studios for producing such a nice movie that I am very fond of. There are a very few select movies I never get bored of watching. And Guardians of the Galaxy is definitely one of my select movies I will always enjoy watching over and over.¬† And last but not least, I loved how Yondu Udonta just smiled at the end of the movie on how he got played again by Peter Quill. I think the moral of that story is that deep down,¬†Yondu knew that it was too dangerous for him to hold onto that Infinity Stone while in his sole possession.

Title: Marvel's Guardians of the Galaxy - Trailer 1 (OFFICIAL)
Comment: Ignore the negative comments about this movie. This movie was great. The only arguments I'm seeing in the comments are coming from major DC fans and you guys like what you like fine, your not the target demographic for a talking raccoon with machine guns or SciFi films with CGI(though I'd like to know how many of you watched Star Wars lately)Others will argue that the story was too "simple" well this movie isn't about that and it isn't about the villain either its about the heroes and watching them grow to become a team and rely on one another. "The jokes were cheesy and lame" or "this movie is for kids" Really? That's opinion based not factual you could ask several comic book fans that are well into their 30s and beyond if this was a good movie they'd say yes. Why? Because this movie gave us what we wanted from a marvel movie and summer movie. Great heroes which is what Marvel does best and great action/comedy. Don't let the opinions of others keep you from seeing this movie. Just my 2 cents on the off chance someone who's never seen this movie reads this.

Title: Marvel's Guardians of the Galaxy - Trailer 1 (OFFICIAL)
Comment: Movie starts out with an intense depressing adult scene you're assuming a big set up for something really important later on, which never really comes. The movie uses the generic plot themes from the big book of "How to make a generic action sci fi movie" and runs with it. No surprises there. There's an occasional attempt to make the characters seem three dimensional with feelings and depth, but it does not work. Best part of the movie is the excellent CGI, action scenes, and a green Zoe Saldana. Would have liked to see more green Zoe Saldana and less of the really annoying CGI racoon thing. Not even attempting to hide the fact the entire movie set up for a sequel always a thumbs down in lazy movie making to me. Get's a C+ from me.

Title: Marvel's Guardians of the Galaxy - Trailer 1 (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
People could easily watch this trailer and think it looks absolutely atrocious, but to be honest, the GotG comics have always been VERY tongue-in-cheek - pretty much just a blend of comedy and mindless, explosive action. So it actually looks like they've pretty much nailed the feel of the comics for this film, which should please a lot of people.
And besides, even if you still don't want to watch it, at least be thankful that this trailer is an honest one and doesn't try to make the film look all intense and dramatic, only to completely let you down when you actually go to see it (*cough* Iron Man 3 *cough*) :P

Comment:
I bet the people hating this are the same ones who walked out on the first arc of Watchmen when it came out. The times I've seen it I see one-fourth of the audience leaving.
Yeah, extensive and numerous fight scenes alone don't make a movie good.
I like humor in my movies too, and GotG is a perfect team to introduce the cosmic (marvel) universe and opens up a TON of possibilities.
They do look goofy, but these are some of the most badass Marvel characters, especially when sh*t goes down (Annihilation/Thanos Imperative, anyone?)
X-Men and Spiderman can try, but they have a long ways to go build up their cinematic universe
